## üåà Why Aura?

Aura is not just a framework‚Äîit's a **human interface to computation**. Write logic, build UIs, and create full applications using nothing but plain English.

- **üó£Ô∏è Natural English Syntax**: No brackets, no semicolons. Just English.
- **üß† Dual-Mode Engine**: 
  - **Core Logic**: Pure Python execution (variables, loops, functions)
  - **UI Mode**: React/Vite web applications with premium design
- **‚ö° Brain-Powered**: Integrated AI (Qwen-0.5B) for intelligent syntax correction.
- **üé® Production-Ready**: Generates optimized, deployable code.

---

## üöÄ Quick Start

### 1. Installation
Ensure you have Python 3.8+ installed.

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/kingenious0/Aura-Programming-Language.git
cd Aura-Programming-Language

# Install in development mode
pip install -e .
```

### 2. Choose Your Mode

#### üß† **Core Logic Mode** (Pure Python)
Create a file `logic.aura`:
```aura
set score to 10

if score > 5
    print "You win!"
else
    print "Try again"

repeat 3 times
    print "Aura is awesome!"
```

Run it:
```bash
aura run logic.aura        # Execute
aura trace logic.aura      # Debug with output
aura compile logic.aura    # Generate Python file
```

#### üåê **UI Mode** (React/Vite)
Initialize a project:
```bash
aura init my-app
cd my-app
```

Create a page `pages/Home.aura`:
```aura
Use the dark theme

Create a heading with the text 'Welcome to the Future'
Create a paragraph with the text 'This page was built using plain English.'

Create a button with the text 'Click Me'
When clicked, display 'Hello from Aura! üéâ'
```

Start developing:
```bash
aura dev
```
Open [http://localhost:5173](http://localhost:5173) to see your app live!

---

## üìù The Aura Language

### Core Logic (Phase 2 - NEW!)
```aura
# Variables
set score to 10
set name to "Aura"

# Math
set total to score * 2

# Conditionals
if total > 15
    print "High score!"

# Loops
repeat 5 times
    print "Hello"

# Functions
define function greet
    print "Welcome to Aura"

call function greet
```

### UI Development (Phase 1)
```aura
Use the dark theme

Create a heading with the text 'Welcome to the Future'
Create a paragraph with the text 'This page was built using plain English.'

Create a button with the text 'Click Me'
When clicked, display 'Hello from Aura! üéâ'
```

---

## üìÇ Project Organization

Aura projects are structured to be neat and intuitive:

- `transpiler/` ‚Äî The core engine logic (Parser, HTML Generator, CLI).
- `docs/` ‚Äî Comprehensive guides and technical specifications.
- `examples/` ‚Äî A library of Aura snippets to learn from.
- `playground/` ‚Äî A pre-configured project to test Aura live.
- `tools/` ‚Äî Utility scripts for debugging and specialized setups.
- `vscode-extension/` ‚Äî Official VS Code support for `.aura` syntax.

---

## üéÆ The Playground

We've included a `playground/` directory so you can try Aura immediately without creating a new project.

```bash
# Go to the playground
cd playground

# Start the dev server
aura dev
```

